	<td>
	  <font size="2" face="Verdana">
		Subject:&nbsp;<b>Questions from a druid</b></font>
		
		<a href="MB_Editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1005570&TN=Questions+from+a+druid&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1005570&PL=4&amp;action=REPLY"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/btn_reply.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Reply to message"></a>
		<br>
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/Icons/icon5.gif" border="0" align="ABSCENTER" width="15" height="15">
		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 7/17/2001 4:21:57 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=42776">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Woodsie Druid" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Woodsie+Druid">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Woodsie Druid" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1005570&TN=Questions+from+a+druid&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1005570&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Hail noble Clerics!</P><P>I have seen that there are some discussions about Druids and Shamans getting XP Rezzes with the new expansion (or in a patch). Could you tell me where this information comes from please?</P><P>Besides that I would like to state my opinion about it:<BR>As a Druid I get bugged for Spirit of the Wolf, Circles, Heals, Buff-spells and powerleveling all the time. Those Ressurection spells would be one more point for boring tells and questions about my duties, so I would rather like to not get those spells (I speak for me and maybe the Druid as a class).</P><P>Fact is that VI works on class balance and they want to break the monopoly of Clerics considering one group spot, this monopoly is based on best heals, best buffs and best rezzes.<BR>With Druids and Shamans getting those spells there would be five classes that can do the job, so why don't they enhance the skills of the existing classes (Paladins and Necromancers) and offer other things to Druids and Shamans to make them group friendly and high-end-game capable?</P><P>As I cannot speak for Shamans I will explain my vision about Druids. These thoughts are not "tested", so they could be a too mighty empowerment - not all points but some would do the job anyways. Please don't flame me for that...</P><P>I would wish...<BR>- that my spells work also in indoor zones (Spirit of the Wolf and Harmony mainly)<BR>- that my buff-spells stack with those from Clerics and Shamans<BR>- that my damageshields would really make a difference against those 12.500+ HP mobs<BR>- this 1.000 HP heal would come at level 55</P><P>In my eyes Druids are a support class, we are not the best healers and not the best buffers, nukers or gaters. But most things should be more comfortable with a Druid in the group and we should be able to ease the job of any caster-specialist (Heals for Clerics, Harmony to help puller and to ease Enchanter's life, and so on).</P><P>If I would be allowed one wish I would ask for something people call identity for this Jack-of-all-trades class. That would be master of damageshields for example - with a highend damageshield that gives some nice AC and does something between 100 and 200 damage per hit).</P><P><BR>Well, sorry. This threat developed to a class whining (I am very concerned about balance as you see). Mixing the skills of classes is the wrong way in my eyes, I'd rather like to see the skills of the so called "unwanted" classes to be enhanced to a "wanted" level and the specialist classes to get some kind of fun skills or spells (no clue though how they should look like).</P><P><BR>Feyaria Draughiril<BR>Wood Elf Druid of Tunare<BR>Officer of the Elven Kingdom<BR>Mithaniel Marr</P><P>Message edited by: Woodsie Druid (7/17/2001 4:21:57 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
