		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Spiddles">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Spiddles" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1005570&TN=Questions+from+a+druid&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1005590&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I dont mind at all that druids/shamans got a rez spell. I'm sure that it wouldnt be as powerfull as a clerics would, but can be considered when there is no cleric around.</P><P>For monopoly I have to disagree.</P><P>1. There is a shortage of clerics is a false statement I think. Most servers have tons of high level clerics and since groups only want one cleric, you will often see many clerics sitting at zones looking for a group.</P><P>In the pre kunark days yes, there was a shortage of clerics. Now that we can goto level 60 things have changed since there is more higher level people and plenty to do even if your lev 60 unlike it was at pre-kunark.</P><P>2. The cleric life is a expensive life. Our buffs cost us 10.5pp a cast (with good charisma) and we dont have the ability to solo for money like a druid or a shaman could. The rez is pretty much the only real money maker for a cleric if they are desperate for cash. Sure we can make money with heals, buffs and binds but what level 49 cleric wants to stand in oasis and heal for gold pieces so he can afford his plate armour or  peridots?</P><P>I can deal with another class geting a rez spell thats not as powerfull as the clerics.<BR>It would take the edge off of trying to find a cleric but wouldnt effect them from being able to make some cash.</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
