		</font>
		<hr size="1">Dear Spiddles,</P><P>I never said that there is a shortage of Clerics, but common sense by now is that any group not only wants one Cleric but cannot play without one since the healing power cannot reached from any others by far, buffing up a tank up to 5k HP is essential to raids and the 6% diffenerence between the 49 and 56 Rez represent hours of playing at upper levels.</P><P>Clerics master all those three vital points and by saying "break the monopoly" I mean that there could be some enhancements that leave Clerics as the best combination of those three skills, but they might be topped in one of them (like Warriors, best melee combination of tanking and damage, but there are classes that top them in damage - Rogue and Monk).</P><P>As it is now, a group cannot go to a highlevel dungeon without a Cleric and an Enchanter, so they wait for hours for them to show up.</P><P>As for costs I think Clerics don't finance themselfes by selling rezzes or their split of coins in KC but by getting invitations to raids all the time since the raid organisation is short of Clerics. Often time they will get an offer for the first high value item that is not quest relevant for someone or by simple lotto of those dropped items. I could imagine that a Cleric could be on a raid every day if the player has some days off from work.</P><P>But again, I don't think that Druids should get Rezzes, if some more classes shall get it, move down the level for Paladins so they get the 90% Rezz at 55 or somewhere like that.<BR>Indoor working spells and the 1.000 HP heal at 55 should help Druids enough, Shamans shall speak for themselves.</P><P>Feyaria Draughiril<BR>MithMarr<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
