		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=37856">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Spiddles" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Spiddles">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Spiddles" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1005570&TN=Questions+from+a+druid&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1005655&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I think giving other classes the ability to be a good healer in a high lev dungeon but not as good as a cleric would be a very difficult thing to do.</P><P>How over powering would it make the druid or shaman? Should they have the ability to solo well and be able to heal well too?</P><P>How much healing power would you have to give them so they can start to compete with a cleric? Our CH is quite powerfull. That 4k hp tank can be healed completely for 6 times in a fight. 6 times would be 32k hp healed by a cleric. For them to be able to make a druid able to be a good healer but not replace the cleric, he is going to need to be able to heal close to that 32k hp.</P><P>To do that they would need to either give you a ton of mana or give you wicked healing spells for low mana cost. A ton of mana would make you a over powered solo'er and low mana healing spells would let you heal more than they would of wanted.</P><P>The only other way would be for them to nerf the complete heal spells of the cleric. Now if they do that, they will have to revamp all the mobs in the game to compinsate and then re-do all the boss mob encounters. That would take alot of money and work for them so I doubt they would do it.</P><P>To give the others the ability to come close to doing a clerics job wouldnt be a simple task to do. You need to be able to do it without making anothher class to over powering and that I think would be harder than it looks.</P><P>For what you want is some of your spells to work indoors and a 1k heal spell.</P><P>The 1k heal spell sounds good to me but it still couldnt possibly compete with the CH.<BR>The bonus is that it would make you a better back up healer and able to keep people alive while the cleric is link dead or ectra. In some cases you could be main healer if the group was pulling slow.<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
