		<hr size="1">True thoughts, Spiddles.</P><P>The vision of VI is that a group at least has a healer, a melee and a caster. Lets split melee into damagedealing and tanking. For calculation reasons I will count two classes as pure support (maybe Druids and Bards), leaving 12 classes. Divided on those four roles, we would have three classes to be able to do each job.</P><P>Since VI only sees those few roles, the groups are limited to six members and specialisation is urgently needed, there must be two other classes that come close to the Cleric in healing power. Reasons for this are that a) many groups have to wait for hours to get their Cleric so they can start to hunt and b) the Cleric as a class is not interesting enough so that 1/6 of the players choose them.</P><P>In my eyes VI doesn't want a complete new skill pool for those 14 classes so they try to reach this goal by increasing the given skills of the existing classes, I mean giving them more skills of a Cleric.</P><P>If those 11 Classes would get the existing - other - skills enhanced (my example was the damageshield for Druids) so they cut a dent in a highlevel XP group one could reach the goal (starting to hunt) with a Shaman as mainhealer, because with the combo Enc-War-Dru-Sha and no matter what other classes mobs would get down that fast that the enormous healing power of a Cleric would not be needed. In case the Druid or Shaman would be a Warrior instead, having a Cleric as healer would be vital again.</P><P>This is not ment as a call for nerfing Clerics or empowering Druids or Shamans. What I mean is that each combination of classes should be able to do the same with their skills - as long as there is any healer, any melee and any caster in the group, outdoor as indoor.</P><P>The game is designed for a group of specialists that know to play their class perfectly. As VI cannot renew all zones and all mobs, they have to get classes into a shape where really each combination of those three categories is able to manage the same progress.</P><P>Just a thought to this...</P><P>A Cleric, Enchanter and Warrior group in a dungeon. Perfect Heals, CC and tanking/dmg. If one member dies he gets a rez and the xp loss is neglectable, they each get one level in six hours of playing.</P><P>Next day. A Shaman, Wizard and Shadow Knight are at the same camp spot. It is a combination of Healer, Caster and Melee as proposed from the vision. They lack a proper CC (there would be only Root), a perfect Healing and tanking/dmg, and no Rez is available. Nevertheless this group should be able to get the same level in the same time. </P><P>Saying that they might rather fit to another camping spot or circumstances is not fair, because the first group fits to all situations.</P><P>Fey<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
